page.title: 15Walking Towards Sheerness
page.content: As we walked we looked at the {landscape}and houses, (most of which were modern and detached) as well as the{beach. On the{cliffs}we saw lots of wild flowers such as red and white clover, yarrow, challock and buttercups. Looking out to{sea}we saw the Olau Line Ferry and there were many other ships such as barges, a dredger and a yawl with all its sails spread. Further along we could see a sand bar which, as it was low tide, we could have walked out to. On the other side of the road is the camp site and some rough grazing used mainly for horses. In the distance we could see Sheerness Steel Mill. We then came to the Catamaran Club.
